,\n&gt;\n&gt; You have it all wrong.\n&gt;\n&gt; Please allow me to explain it. A little bit of context from my side will\n&gt; help you understand why i am saying what i am saying.\n&gt;\n&gt; Back in 2012, i was in a severe mental torture because what i want to\n&gt; happen in life is not happening. I visited few astrologers with my question\n&gt; in the beginning of 2013. They said that the certain planet is weak in my\n&gt; horoscope and it is creating obstruction and i need to chant mantra for it.\n&gt;\n&gt; I started chanting mantra. The chanting of mantra created hope in me. The\n&gt; hope that things will eventually settle down.\n&gt;\n&gt; It has been one year of chanting the mantra. I am still chanting it.\n&gt; Everyday. It has been 365 * 108 = 39,420 times i have chanted few mantras.\n&gt;\n&gt; Did anything change from Feb 2013 till now since i started chanting the\n&gt; mantras ? No.\n&gt;\n&gt; Do i still chant mantra ? Yes.\n&gt;\n&gt; Why do i still chant mantra if things are not working out ? Hope. Hope.\n&gt; Hope. Hope that things will work out eventually.\n&gt;\n&gt; Do i want mantra to fail ? No. I want mantra to succeed as it is my only\n&gt; last hope. However, i have not received any success yet.\n&gt;\n&gt; The day i will get success, i will be the forerunner in promoting the\n&gt; mantra-chanting.\n&gt;\n&gt; Right now, there is no success. Therefore, i can not say that mantra\n&gt; chanting is the &#39;Ramban&#39;.\n&gt;\n&gt; Thanks\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;   On Wednesday, February 19, 2014 6:07 PM, Kannan Iyengar &lt;\n&gt; prof.kannan.iyengar@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt;   Namasttay,\n&gt; 1.       There is a psychology behind this.\n&gt; 2.       When one observes whether something is working or not, he has\n&gt; already created a possibility of &quot;not working&quot; in his mind at the outset.\n&gt; This is called self-indoctrination or bias or polarization.\n&gt; 3.       As long as the mind is booted with the thought of possibility of\n&gt; &quot;not working&quot;, it creates a justifying circumstances of its own to prove\n&gt; its thought.\n&gt; 4.       I am finding difficult to explain. But I will try.\n&gt; 5.       Let me explain again in another words.\n&gt; 6.       When the mind is booted with a thought of possibility of &quot;not\n&gt; working&quot;, it has created something. A thought is a creation. Now just like\n&gt; a mother protects her baby, likewise a mind will always seek to protect its\n&gt; thought which is its baby, its creation. So, the mind then will send out\n&gt; energies appropriately in the universe, so as to make this possibility of\n&gt; &quot;not working&quot;, a justifiable reality. And surely that will be the reality.\n&gt; It will be easily proven with facts that it is indeed &quot;not working&quot;. The\n&gt; mind then rejoices at its success, and hardens its belief system.\n&gt; 7.       Under such indoctrinated or polarized or biased mind system, the\n&gt; reality will manifest, according to the belief of the mind.\n&gt; 8.       Once this belief hardens, the mind keeps hell bent to propagate\n&gt; it. And this becomes propaganda. In Sanskruta we call it Vimoodha or Moodha\n&gt; meaning a mind becoming hardened to such an extent, that it blocks all\n&gt; intellectual gateways, that is, it completely silences Buddhi or intellect\n&gt; or capacity to think logically and neutrally without any bias.\n&gt; 9.       This is basically a sick mind for which there is a special\n&gt; treatment ordained by the divine, where all sick mind goes for treatment\n&gt; for permanent cure. There is a place called hell administered by Yama\n&gt; Dharma-Raaja where all kinds of psycho-spiritual treatment is given in a\n&gt; unique way for the upliftment of the sick souls.\n&gt; 10.   The company of wise people is the only tonic for sick minds. The\n&gt; wise people have enhanced spiritual energy surrounding their body, which is\n&gt; also called Grace-Light. This Grace-Light is very powerful and it can\n&gt; pierce any hardened layer of sick mind, and awaken the dead or sleeping\n&gt; intellect, and enlighten it.\n&gt; 11.   Once the sleeping intellect is awakened, then that intellect will\n&gt; nourish the sick mind to the appropriate path, thus saving it from going to\n&gt; the mental hospital called hell.\n&gt; 12.   Saadhu Sangati Parama Durlabha, meaning the company of wise is a\n&gt; very rare gift. When God is pleased with us, he blesses us with the company\n&gt; of wise. Wise men are verily the temple of God, for, in their heart resides\n&gt; The God.\n&gt; 13.   Shri Krishna Himself says in Bhaagavatam, that he runs behind such\n&gt; wise people, so that the dust of their feet can fall on him and make him\n&gt; blessed.\n&gt; 14.   Shri MahaaVishnu is a Bhakta Vatsala, meaning caring and loving to\n&gt; devotees, and a Braahmana Priya, meaning a lover and seeker of wise people.\n&gt; 15.   Let us prostrate before our Beloved Naaraayana to forgive us, and\n&gt; keep blessing us with the Grace-Light in the form of company of wise.\n&gt; 16.   Aum Na-mo Naa-raa-ya-naa-ya\n&gt; Aum Shaantih Shaantih Shaantih\n&gt;\n&gt; With Kind Regards,\n&gt; Kannan\n&gt;\n&gt;  *From:* vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com [mailto:vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com]\n&gt; *On Behalf Of *Phil Stinnet\n&gt; *Sent:* Thursday, February 20, 2014 4:50 AM\n&gt; *To:* vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\n&gt; *Subject:* Re: [vedic-wisdom] Significance of chanting Namakam/ Chamakam\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;    &quot;Mantra chanting or stotra chanting have almost same beneficial\n&gt; effects&quot;\n&gt;\n&gt;  I am chanting few mantra for last one year as per the recommendations\n&gt; from several astrologers. Not a one dime of effect in my life.\n&gt;\n&gt;  However, defenders of mantra will say -\n&gt;\n&gt;  1) Your past-karma must be too bad.\n&gt;  2) The mantra needs to be energized.\n&gt;  3) You are chanting the wrong mantra.\n&gt;\n&gt;  However, Mantra-chantin